Armenia: Adana Massacre: An estimated 15,000–30,000 are killed.
Australia: The first powered aeroplane flight in Australia is made.
Belgium: Death of Leopold II, King of the Belgians
Accession of Albert I as King of the Belgians
Cuba: U.S. occupation ends. José Miguel Gómez of the Liberal Party becomes president.
Kenya: Witchcraft is illegal in East Africa
Malaysia: The Anglo-Siamese Treaty of 1909 was signed by the United Kingdom and Thailand, effectively dissecting the northern Malay states.
Sweden: The Stockholm School of Economics (Handelshögskolan i Stockholm) is founded.
The General Strike of 1909 (Swedish General Strike).
USA: William Howard Taft implemented Dollar Diplomacy.
The NAACP was founded by W. E. B. Du Bois.
Robert Peary became the first person to reach the North Pole.
The first redesigned Lincoln Penny was released to the public.
